oakcurric:unit-3176
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Numbers: 'il y a', plural nouns"@en ;
  curric:slug "numbers-il-y-a-plural-nouns" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils learn numbers 1-12 and the plural indefinite article 'des'
  meaning some. They add -s to form plural nouns and learn that the irregular verb phrase
  'il y a' means there is, there are. Pupils combine these knowledge components to talk
  about how many of things there are."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit expands pupils' knowledge from singular to plural noun forms,
  and introduces essential knowledge of numbers 1-12 and the plural indefinite article 'some'.
  This extends pupils' communicative range, embedding many previously taught nouns, whilst
  enabling pupils to talk about more than one. Pupils also extend liaison to -s and -x, e.g.,
  trois oranges, deux enfants, whilst reapplying knowledge of silent final consonants in plural
  noun final -s. In other units, pupils will build on number knowledge to communicate
  effectively about ages and dates.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3176-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3176-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3176-3 ;
  curric:id "3176"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.688725Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-listen-and-respond-to-songs-and-rhymes ,
    oakcurric:thread-nouns-and-determiners .

oakcurric:unit-3180
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "People, places, things: adjective agreement, subject pronouns 'it'"@en ;
  curric:slug "people-places-things-adjective-agreement-subject-pronouns-it" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils use prior knowledge of 'avoir' and 'être' in cultural
  contexts: Mother's Day in Francophonie, the cartoon Tintin, and also the context of a trip
  to the zoo. New knowledge includes the subject pronouns for 'it', 'il' and 'elle''. Silent
  Final e, ç/c, -ien, and qu are introduced."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already know that adjectives agree for gender. In this unit,
  they learn that many adjectives follow the noun, whilst in English they come before it. This
  unit builds upon pupils' prior knowledge of noun gender, teaching that the French pronouns
  for 'it' match noun gender, so that 'il' is both 'he' and 'it', and 'elle' is 'she' and 'it'.
  Securing pupils' use of singular forms of verbs 'be, being' and 'have, having' in multiple
  contexts, this unit is solid preparation for future units, which introduce plural persons of
  these essential verbs.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3180-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3180-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3180-3 ;
  curric:id "3180"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.691175Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-adjectives ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-nouns-and-determiners ,
    oakcurric:thread-verb-to-have-having ,
    oakcurric:thread-verb-to-be-being ,
    oakcurric:thread-use-reference-resources .

oakcurric:unit-3186
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "What I and others have: plural 'avoir' and nouns"@en ;
  curric:slug "what-i-and-others-have-plural-avoir-and-nouns" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils use singular and plural postnominal adjectives and 'avoir' in
  the contexts of an online exchange, conversations between cousins in France and Haiti, and
  physical description of hair and eyes. Supporting sounds are Silent Final e and -s
  liaison."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit continues to build on prior singular and plural verb knowledge,
  introducing plural 'avoir'. Liaison with -s and Silent Final e are important complementary
  sound-symbol correspondences. Postnominal adjectives, including plural forms, are revisited
  and anchored in new contexts, including physical description. Later in the unit, high
  frequency adjectives that come before the noun are introduced. The unit brings language
  together in an extended description of a friend.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3186-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3186-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3186-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3186-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3186-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3186-6 ;
  curric:id "3186"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.693521Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-ask-and-answer-spoken-questions ,
    oakcurric:thread-nouns-and-determiners ,
    oakcurric:thread-verb-to-have-having ,
    oakcurric:thread-adjectives ,
    oakcurric:thread-verb-to-be-being ,
    oakcurric:thread-read-and-respond-to-texts .

oakcurric:unit-3189
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "What I and others do: 'faire' singular persons, qu'est-ce que"@en ;
  curric:slug "what-i-and-others-do-faire-singular-persons-quest-ce-que" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils use singular 'faire' and 'jouer' to talk about activities and
  sports. They extend sentences, using subordinate clauses with 'quand'. and use 'qu'est-ce
  que' and quel/quelle to ask what sports others do. Pupils further embed knowledge of a
  range of previously learnt sounds."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit further develops pupils' verb lexicon, introducing singular
  forms of the high frequency verb 'faire' to do, make, with negation and 'qu'est-ce que'
  questions, before introducting its idiomatic use with weather expressions. Singular 'faire'
  and 'jouer' with different sports are also taught, along with plural possessives 'mes, tes'.
  Building on pupils’ use of simple and compound sentences, pupils learn to create longer
  sentences with subordinate clauses, using ‘quand’, when.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3189-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3189-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3189-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3189-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3189-5 ;
  curric:id "3189"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.781651Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-written-production ,
    oakcurric:thread-ask-and-answer-spoken-questions ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-negation ,
    oakcurric:thread-nouns-and-determiners ,
    oakcurric:thread-read-and-respond-to-texts .

oakcurric:unit-3178
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Activities: singular regular -ER verbs"@en ;
  curric:slug "activities-singular-regular-er-verbs" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, in the contexts of the Menton Carnival and family activities, pupils
  deepen their knowledge of different 'e' sounds, practise uses 'de' and use -er verbs in
  the present. They use prior knowledge of adjective agreement to describe photos of
  Menton's colourful citrus fruit sculptures."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit teaches pupils that 'de' means of, as well as its frequent uses
  conveying possession, e.g, La sœur de Pierre, and in compounds, e.g., La fête de Menton.
  Later pupils learn that 'de' also means 'from'. Pupils will already have begun to build a
  repertoire of -er verbs. In this unit, they learn that French singular present tense forms
  translate both simple and ongoing present tense in English. Later, pupils will extend this
  knowledge to plural present tense forms and in new contexts. Knowledge of adjective gender
  agreement and all 'e' sounds is strengthened.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3178-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3178-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3178-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3178-4 ;
  curric:id "3178"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.839427Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-nouns-and-determiners ,
    oakcurric:thread-adjectives .

oakcurric:unit-3175
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "What I and others do: singular regular -er verbs"@en ;
  curric:slug "what-i-and-others-do-singular-regular-er-verbs" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils use -er infinitive and singular forms to talk about activities
  in school and at home. New sounds are complemetary er/é/ez, and contrastive eu, è/ê. New
  vocabulary is selected for its frequency and contexts, and pupils anchor previously taught
  vocabulary in new contexts."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit extends pupils' verb knowledge as building a verb lexicon is
  essential early knowledge. First, pupils learn some high frequency regular -er verbs and how
  these translate two ways into English, e.g., 'to listen' and 'listening'. Related phonics
  include er/é/ez and contrastive eu, è/ê. Next, pupils learn singular forms of -er verbs to
  talk about what they and others do. Knowledge of determiners extends to definite articles and
  possessives 'mon, ma, ton, ta'. Practice in several contexts anchors this new knowledge,
  which pupils will later secure and develop in further contexts.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3175-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3175-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3175-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3175-4 ;
  curric:id "3175"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.016911Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-nouns-and-determiners .

oakcurric:unit-3185
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Celebrations in France and Haiti: plural -ER verbs, est-ce que, negation"@en ;
  curric:slug "celebrations-in-france-and-haiti-plural-er-verbs-est-ce-que-negation" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils use plural -er verbs, negation and est-ce que questions to
  ask and answer about important festivals in France and Haiti, including Christmas, New
  Year, Haitian Independence, 'La Chandeleur' and Mardi Gras. Knowledge of key 'e' sounds is
  strengthened."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already have learnt plural pronouns and 'être'. This unit
  builds verb knowledge, introducing plural -er verbs and ne...pas negation. Having secured
  intonation questions, this unit teaches est-ce que questions. Together these new structures
  expand pupils' communicative repertoire substantially, appropriate to the depth of new
  cultural content in the unit. Key sound-symbol correspondences are further secured through
  activities that contrast two similar sounds.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3185-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3185-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3185-3 ;
  curric:id "3185"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.187470Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-ask-and-answer-spoken-questions ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-negation ,
    oakcurric:thread-listen-and-respond-to-songs-and-rhymes .

oakcurric:unit-3181
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "What I and others like doing: 2-verb phrases"@en ;
  curric:slug "what-i-and-others-like-doing-2-verb-phrases" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils learn to use 2-verb structures to communicate effectively
  about activities they and their friends like doing at school at school. They also extend
  their phonics knowledge with new sounds -tion and r."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Building on secure knowledge of singular present -er verbs, this unit
  introduces 2-verb structures with 'aimer' to like. Further increasing pupils' communicative
  repertoire, this unit adds plural definite article 'les' to pupils' prior knowledge of
  singular 'le' and 'la' and introduces two new sounds -tion and r. Towards the end of the
  unit, pupils bring together prior knowledge and new learning to write a short message, making
  use of reference resources to personalise their work.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3181-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3181-2 ;
  curric:id "3181"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.324068Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-ask-and-answer-spoken-questions ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-nouns-and-determiners ,
    oakcurric:thread-use-reference-resources ,
    oakcurric:thread-read-and-respond-to-texts .

oakcurric:unit-3184
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Me and others: plural 'être' and regular adjectives"@en ;
  curric:slug "me-and-others-plural-etre-and-regular-adjectives" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, in the context of school, pupils use singular and plural 'être' and
  adjectives, numbers 16-31 and intonation questions to understand a story, describe
  teachers and friends, talk about birthdays and important cultural dates. Several key
  sound-symbol correspondences are revisited."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Where several previous units have anchored pupil knowledge of singular
  'être', this unit teaches plural forms and plural adjective agreement, in the context of
  school. Having already learnt to ask questions with interrogatives 'quoi' and 'quand', pupils
  here revisit 'comment' and add 'qui' to their question repertoire. Plural pronouns 'ils' and
  'elles', they, are now applied to objects as well as people. Pupils also learn numbers 16-31
  which enable them to talk about dates. This introduction to plural present tense French verbs
  is extended in later units with plural 'avoir' and -er verbs.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3184-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3184-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3184-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3184-4 ;
  curric:id "3184"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.394837Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
