oakcurric:unit-3177
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Introductions: singular 'être', 'avoir', and regular adjectives"@en ;
  curric:slug "introductions-singular-etre-avoir-and-regular-adjectives" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils embed vowel and other sounds. They secure numbers 1-12 and
  essential verbs to be, to have and there are, describing themselves, friends and a
  monster. Pupils learn that 'avoir' also means 'be' for ages and states, enabling them to
  say with more precision how they feel."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already have learnt singular forms of essential verbs '’être’,
  ’avoir’ and 'il y a'. In this unit, knowledge of these verbs, regular adjectives and
  possessives 'mon, ma, ton, ta' is anchored in the context of making friends. Pupils then
  learn that 'avoir', also means 'be', broadening their communicative range to age and states
  e.g., cold. As well as securing numbers 1-12, pupils expand their range of high frequency
  words, learning months of the year, and several parts of the body. In a later unit, pupils
  will learn adjective placement after nouns with these core verbs.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3177-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3177-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3177-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3177-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3177-5 ;
  curric:id "3177"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.782127Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-2 ;
