oakcurric:unit-3179
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "What I and others like: opinion verbs"@en ;
  curric:slug "what-i-and-others-like-opinion-verbs" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils learn singular persons of new -er verbs ‘aimer’ to like and
  ‘préférer’ to prefer to express likes and preferences. They use reference resources to
  personalise their responses, researching new nouns. Pupils also develop phonics, learning
  a new spelling [ai] for the [ê/è] sound."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Having previously practised the identical sound written [ê] and [è], this
  unit teaches [ai] which has the same sound. Pupils also add to their er-verb lexicon with two
  new verbs. Asking for and giving opinions and preferences extends pupils' communicative
  repertoire, and is supported by opportunities to research new nouns in order to give more
  individual responses. Opinion verbs in French require definite articles where they are not
  used in English, so this unit provides a further opportunity for pupils to embed these in a
  more challenging context, which they will revisit again later.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3179-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3179-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3179-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3179-4 ;
  curric:id "3179"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.588132Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present .

oakcurric:unit-3174
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "What I and others have: singular 'avoir' and nouns"@en ;
  curric:slug "what-i-and-others-have-singular-avoir-and-nouns" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit a dream, a story and packing a bag offer multiple contexts for
  learning that nouns have grammatical gender and that this determines the word for a/an.
  Pupils learn to use c'est, it is, with liaison, and singular forms of the verb ‘avoir’.
  Key sounds learnt are un, on, ch, au, u and ou."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit introduces the gateway concept of grammatical gender so pupils
  can use indefinite articles and nouns to identify them, using prior knowledge of 'est' in the
  new phrase 'c'est', it is. Liaison with -t is important complementary phonics, together with
  nasal sounds un, on, and ch, eau/au, u and ou. Pupils then apply noun knowledge, including
  favourite animals sought in reference resources, with singular persons of new verb 'avoir',
  to have, learning questions with interrogative 'quoi' to ask what others have. In another
  unit pupils will extend singular noun knowledge to plural nouns.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3174-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3174-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3174-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3174-4 ;
  curric:id "3174"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.845278Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-ask-and-answer-spoken-questions ,
    oakcurric:thread-nouns-and-determiners ,
    oakcurric:thread-verb-to-have-having ,
    oakcurric:thread-verb-to-be-being ,
    oakcurric:thread-use-reference-resources ,
    oakcurric:thread-questions .

oakcurric:unit-3188
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Where I am going: 'aller' singular persons, où est-ce que"@en ;
  curric:slug "where-i-am-going-aller-singular-persons-ou-est-ce-que" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils use singular 'aller' to go, going. Focusing on another
  Francophone location, Canada, pupils use 'où est-ce que' and prepositions 'dans' and 'à'
  to ask and answer questions about location and destination. Complementary words are places
  in the town and points of the compass."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit introduces pupils to singular forms of the high frequency verb
  'aller' to go, going. Important complementary knowledge that 'dans' and 'à' can both mean
  'in' and 'to', depending on the verb used in the sentence, 'aller' or 'être' is introduced,
  alongside points of the compass. Having already learnt the structure 'est-ce que' for yes/no
  questions, pupils now add the interrogative 'où' to ask and answer questions about location
  and destination. Phonics for this unit appropriately contrast ai with a and (a)in.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3188-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3188-2 ;
  curric:id "3188"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.893688Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-questions .

oakcurric:unit-3173
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Me and others: singular 'être' and regular adjectives"@en ;
  curric:slug "me-and-others-singular-etre-and-regular-adjectives" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, in the context of the classroom, pupils use statements and
  intonation questions to talk about how people are, what they are like, and days of the
  week, using singular 'être' and high frequency adjectives. They learn key sounds a, e, i,
  o, u, eu, an, en and silent final consonants."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit introduces essential early knowledge: the verb ‘être’ to be; the
  sound-symbol correspondences a,e, i, o, u, eu, the nasal sound an/en, and silent final
  consonants. Singular regular adjective agreement for gender is key knowledge for describing
  self and others effectively and high frequency vocabulary is selected to support this
  communicative aim. Greetings enable them to initiate first interactions in French and a
  Christmas lesson anchors key sounds. In another unit, pupils extend their knowledge of
  adjective agreement and apply it to grammatically gendered nouns.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3173-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3173-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3173-3 ;
  curric:id "3173"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.581680Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-2 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-ask-and-answer-spoken-questions ,
    oakcurric:thread-listen-and-respond-to-songs-and-rhymes ,
    oakcurric:thread-adjectives ,
    oakcurric:thread-verb-to-be-being ,
    oakcurric:thread-questions .

